{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"Persist the finding PROSE in the `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar so a remediation re-review can hand\nthe Pass-2 novelty sub-call its own prior findings. Today `build_payload._slim`\n(`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py`) keeps fingerprints/decision/verification but DROPS\n`finding`/`suggested_fix`/`checklist_item`. Add them (observability-only; the surfaced\nverdict shape is untouched) plus a \"latest REVIEW_RESULT for a ticket\" reader. This is NEW\nsidecar infrastructure, not an existing capability.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `_slim` persists `finding`, `suggested_fix`, `checklist_item` (sidecar event only) in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py`\n- [ ] A \"latest REVIEW_RESULT for a ticket\" reader is added (new)\n- [ ] A test pins the surfaced library/MCP/CLI verdict shape is byte-unchanged\n- [ ] The `RETAIN_PER_TICKET` prune bound and reducer-ignored forward-compat rollout are respected"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782755364971831001,"uuid":"013a7011-2eff-4b2e-b373-8fc5c08b14a8"}